				"# If you use the GGUF quantized variants of WAN2.2, use the Unet GGUF node instead, obviously. However, I find that the fp8_scaled versions by Comfy provide both better quality and faster generation times (by fitting into VRAM more I think).\n# 如果你使用的是GGUF量化版本的WAN2.2，显然应该使用Unet GGUF节点。然而，我发现Comfy提供的fp8_scaled版本在质量和生成速度上都更优（我认为这是因为它们更适合VRAM）。\n# You can find the fp8_scaled variants by Comfy [here](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/Wan_2.2_ComfyUI_Repackaged/tree/main/split_files/diffusion_models)!"
