			"color":"#432",
			"widgets_values":[
				"# You can optionally add other LoRa's beside the Lightx2v one, but make sure you add it to both the High-noise and Low-noise models. \n\n# I find that upping the High-noise LoRa strength to 3 works best, IF IT IS A LORA TRAINED ON WAN2.1, but keep the Low-noise LoRa strength at 1. This is at least true with my specific sampler settings.\n\n# IF THE HIGH-NOISE LORA IS INSTEAD ONE ALREADY TRAINED ON WAN2.2, USE A STRENGTH LEVEL OF 1 INSTEAD JUST LIKE THE LOW-NOISE VERSION!\n\n# If you don't want to use any other LoRa's, just disable or remove those nodes.\n\n# The example LoRa shown here is a WAN2.2 version of my Smartphone photo style LoRa, which you can find along with its WAN2.1 version as well as a bunch of other LoRa's by me under my following CivitAI account, if you want to use them:\n\n# [My CivitAI account with a bunch of WAN2.1 and FLUX LoRa's and soon also WAN2.2 LoRa's](https://civitai.com/user/AI_Characters/models).\n\n# Keep an eye out there for any future WAN2.2 LoRa's I may post on their own page!\n\n# 您可选择性地添加其他LoRa模块（除Lightx2v外），但务必确保将其同时添加到高噪声和低噪声模型中。  \n\n# 我发现将高噪声LoRa的强度调整为3效果最佳，但前提是该LoRa模块是在WAN2.1上训练的，而低噪声LoRa的强度应保持为1。这至少适用于我的特定采样器设置。  \n\n# 如果高噪声LoRa实际上是已训练在WAN2.2上的版本，则应将其强度设置为1，与低噪声版本一致！  \n\n# 如果不想使用其他LoRa，只需禁用或移除这些节点。"
			],
